data.chText: （到期）未付的，未做的，未还的；过期的
data.enText: not paid, done, returned, etc. by the required or expected time

data.chText: 逾期的欠款；逾期未还的图书
她的胎儿已超过预产期两周了。
data.enText: Her baby is two weeks overdue.

data.chText: 这辆汽车早就该维修了。
data.enText: This car is overdue for a service.

data.chText: 早该发生的；早应完成的
data.enText: that should have happened or been done before now

data.chText: 像这样的书早就该有人出版了。
data.enText: A book like this is long overdue .

tr: not paid at the scheduled time

value.def: If you say that a change or an event is overdue, you mean that you think it should have happened before now.

example.ex: I'll go home and pay an overdue visit to my mother.
example.tran: 我将回家看望母亲，其实我早该回去了。

value.def: Overdue sums of money have not been paid, even though it is later than the date on which they should have been paid.

example.ex: Teachers have joined a strike aimed at forcing the government to pay overdue salaries and allowances.
example.tran: 教师加入了旨在迫使政府支付拖欠薪水和津贴的罢工。

value.def: An overdue library book has not been returned to the library, even though the date on which it should have been returned has passed.
